    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "1. Electromagnetic Powder Clutch."
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "The electromagnetic powder clutch operates on basic principles of physics \u2013 electricity and magnetism. When iron powder is magnetised, the particles become linked in chain fashion, and the powder, put simply, \"solidifies\". If a small gap between driving and driven members is filled with powder, and current applied to it, then the members become connected and transmission torque (drive) is generated. The transmission torque is proportional to the amount of current supplied.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "Current is supplied via coils located in the driven member. When the current flow is cut off, the transmission torque disappears.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
